  "note" : [{
    "authorReference" : {
      "reference" : "urn:uuid:b4ac89c5-6589-417f-beef-d3fb1ef9c70f",
      "display" : "Mikael Rinnetmäki, the patient"
    },
    "text" : "I disagree with this diagnosis. The earlier diagnosis of dysphonia due to vocal cord problems is correct. For this diagnosis, I got a prescription for reflux medication, which I did not get. For the earlier diagnosis, I was supposed to get voice therapy, but got this other diagnosis instead. What actually helped was that I started to sing in a choir. Whenever I take a longer break from singing, the symptoms come back. When I start singing again, the symptoms go away."
